Taba is a distributed metrics aggregator, similar in concept to statsd. Built with Python using Redis, gevent, and Cython, it currently handles over 6M events/sec with strong consistency guarantees. This talk will present an overview of its design, and discuss the challenges and solutions encountered in the process of building a high throughput, low latency distributed service.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Kevin Ballard</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2014 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/2662/pushing-python-building-a-high-throughput-low-l</guid><enclosure url="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k8YtaSMv-Nc" length="None" type="video/flv"></enclosure><media:thumbnail url="http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/k8YtaSMv-Nc/hqdefault.jpg"></media:thumbnail></item></channel></rss>